  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In patients with percutaneous endoscopic gastrostomy (PEG) delayed gastric emptying has been
      speculated as a cause of aspiration pneumonia. Elemental diet may facilitate gastric emptying
      in PEG patients as compared with regular liquid enteral nutrients, resulting in the
      prevention of aspiration pneumonia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
